document_title: Stage 1 breast cancer: Signs, diagnosis and treatment
subsection_content:
Signs of stage 1 breast cancer may not be obvious, but if present, symptoms often include the following.
Nipple discharge;; Sunken skin;; Swollen or red breasts;; A lump in the breast or armpit;; Changes in texture of breast skin;; Flat nipples;; Unexplained weight loss.
Warning signs of breast cancer
